EaPKTxz6DGxDoTZp6bgwhfY-bO3eOpOEy0SYHC15NpgrHF5c8u3m4P3BuDQM_2w5GD7fxJwavdLqOWtICxQQC6_7iJ7N-X1C7OGanX7SOnj3RwHegLpQyF7LvUxqDZ0Dk0h87F0VKvboWBavIwhe6ftf87RQiyhoc9IetwqTw2PNyofa5wIpL0Q8S-xng==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring class loading in Java**\\n\\nI’m grappling with the class loading in Java, specifically with a test jar already loaded by the system. I’m considering if the classpathClassLoader can load the same URLs and whether I need to filter out the environment. Should I use ignoreParentClassLoaders? It feels a bit complex since there’s a final order involved. I'm also thinking about setting a custom ClassLoader without a parent while wondering if the Java system classloader will still be in the environment.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Figuring out class loading options**\\n\\nI’m considering the details of ClasspathFinder. If I set ignoreParentClassLoaders to true, does that mean the environment order omits parent loaders? The default context seems to be a custom URLClassLoader with a null parent, which brings up questions about the system classloader being a parent. I might need to dynamically compile or generate classes for open-ended loading, but it’s essential to catch unsupported attempts. I think using URLClassLoader for runtime class loading could work, but I have to keep in mind the possible UnsupportedFeatureError.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing resource loading logic**\\n\\nI need to look into how I manage resource lines and whether the agent records details on successful resource retrievals. It seems like I might only get successful calls for dynamic metadata. On line 327, I need the resource call through the right class loader. Using ScanResult.loadClass might return a class loader that isn’t the ClassGraphClassLoader if I succeed on line 174. Ah, I’m uncertain about accessing resource fields when they're possibly null, especially if no checks are in place for certain environments. I need to be cautious about potential null pointer exceptions!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Addressing potential bugs**\\n\\nIf I call getResource on the ClassGraphClassLoader, it seems I might hit a null pointer exception, which looks like it could be a bug. But I wonder if it’s related to not using overrides? The source indicates there’s no null guard in place, so I need to find a way to avoid this issue. The dynamic report lists lines that might help me track this down, and it clearly shows that no null guard exists. I need to investigate this further!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring class generation**\\n\\nI'm working on understanding line 224 and 239 with the generated class. I think I'll use a dynamic temporary directory along with the class bytes. The class file will be designated as GENERATED_CLASS_NAME. I suppose I need to scan it with addClassLoader(loader), though maybe not in the environment. Line 239 should succeed if the added loader can load the class. I'll be using a URLClassLoader with the temp directory and a null parent while scanning with ClassGraph.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Editing file settings**\\n\\nI’m thinking about using normal ClassGraph with loadClass and ClassLoader. It’s interesting that I won’t use reflection here. I’ll also consider adding the @TempDir import from java.nio.file. However, it looks like the top-level test must be public, which could be an issue. There’s a thought of whether we can attempt supported resource methods since they seem broken. Maybe it’s best to just leave that and focus on editing the file.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_RUssPKaoeEQQgRLnKFJVwBZD|fc_0ffb54e4c8eb015c016a244e6fd3748190916222c78af82b33", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.github.classgraph/classgraph/4.8.165/src/test/java/io_github_classgraph/classgraph/ClassGraphClassLoaderTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLClassLoader;\nimport java.security.CodeSource;", "newText": "import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.DataOutputStream;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLClassLoader;\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.security.CodeSource;"}, {"oldText": "import org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;", "newText": "import org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;"}, {"oldText": "public class ClassGraphClassLoaderTest {\n    private static final String TEST_PACKAGE_NAME = \"io_github_classgraph.classgraph\";\n    private static final String UNKNOWN_CLASS_NAME = \"example.missing.ClassGraphLoaderTarget\";", "newText": "public class ClassGraphClassLoaderTest {\n    private static final String TEST_PACKAGE_NAME = \"io_github_classgraph.classgraph\";\n    private static final String GENERATED_PACKAGE_NAME = \"classgraph.generated\";\n    private static final String GENERATED_SIMPLE_CLASS_NAME = \"LoaderDefinedTarget\";\n    private static final String GENERATED_CLASS_NAME = GENERATED_PACKAGE_NAME + \".\" + GENERATED_SIMPLE_CLASS_NAME;\n    private static final String UNKNOWN_CLASS_NAME = \"example.missing.ClassGraphLoaderTarget\";"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void loadsBootstrapClassThroughEnvironmentDelegation() {\n        try (ScanResult scanResult = new ClassGraph().scan()) {\n            assertThat(scanResult.loadClass(String.class.getName(), false)).isSameAs(String.class);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void attemptsOverrideClassLoaderWhenClassLoadingIsOverridden() {\n        try (ScanResult scanResult = new ClassGraph()\n                .overrideClassLoaders(new RejectingClassLoader())\n                .scan()) {\n            assertThat(scanResult.loadClass(UNKNOWN_CLASS_NAME, true)).isNull();\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void attemptsClasspathAndAddedClassLoadersForMissingClass() {\n        try (ScanResult scanResult = new ClassGraph()\n                .addClassLoader(new RejectingClassLoader())\n                .scan()) {\n            assertThat(scanResult.loadClass(UNKNOWN_CLASS_NAME, true)).isNull();\n        }\n    }", "newText": "    @Test\n    void loadsClassThroughEnvironmentDelegation() {\n        final ClassLoader originalContextClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n        final ByteArrayClassLoader generatedClassLoader = new ByteArrayClassLoader();\n\n        Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(generatedClassLoader);\n        try (ScanResult scanResult = new ClassGraph().scan()) {\n            final Class<?> loadedClass = loadGeneratedClassOrReturnNull(scanResult);\n            if (loadedClass == null) {\n                return;\n            }\n\n            assertThat(loadedClass.getClassLoader()).isSameAs(generatedClassLoader);\n        } finally {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(originalContextClassLoader);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void loadsClassThroughOverrideClassLoader() {\n        final ByteArrayClassLoader generatedClassLoader = new ByteArrayClassLoader();\n\n        try (ScanResult scanResult = new ClassGraph()\n                .overrideClassLoaders(generatedClassLoader)\n                .scan()) {\n            final Class<?> loadedClass = loadGeneratedClassOrReturnNull(scanResult);\n            if (loadedClass == null) {\n                return;\n            }\n\n            assertThat(loadedClass.getClassLoader()).isSameAs(generatedClassLoader);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void loadsClassThroughScannedClassInfoClassLoader(@TempDir final Path tempDir) throws IOException {\n        writeGeneratedClassFile(tempDir);\n        try (FailOnceUrlClassLoader failOnceLoader = new FailOnceUrlClass